*Italian: [[livido]] ''m''
{{bottom}}

'''mark on fruit'''
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[rotte]] [[plek]] (a ''bruise''), [[beurs]] (it is ''bruised'')
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|bruis|ing}}

# To [[strike]] (a person) so as to give them a bruise or bruises.
# To cause fruit to bruise (''see intransitive definition'').

====Translations====
'''strike (a person), giving them a bruise'''
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[slaan]]
{{mid}}
*French: [[contusionner]], [[meurtrir]]
{{bottom}}

'''cause fruit to bruise'''
{{top}}
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-verb|bruis|ing}}

# Of fruit, to gain bruises through being handled [[roughly]].
#:''Bananas bruise easily.''

====Translations====
'''of fruit, to gain bruises'''
{{top}}
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

